The paper deals with the problem of routing messages in wireless sensor networks, which is a topic in computer networks (cs.NI). The main focus of the paper is on the geometric properties of the graphs involved, specifically their embedding in the Euclidean plane (cs.CG). The paper also uses techniques from graph theory and combinatorics (cs.DM) to characterize the trees that admit a greedy embedding. Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the greedy embedding strategy, which is a topic in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and could also be relevant to the design of wireless sensor networks (cs.SI).
